I came here for the first time to watch one of the England games during the World Cup. The atmosphere was great - they had a whole tent and festive banners set up outside paired with misters to help combat the heat. I, however, made a poor choice as far as food goes. The grilled cheese was very "meh" and I should have gone with the good ol' fish and chips like my friend (I tried a bite -- they were fantastic).   One of my favorite parts of this little spot is the artwork on the walls. From James Bond to The Clash to A Clockwork Orange, I have to say it all adds to the experience. I'd definitely give it another shot because we spent hours in there and had plenty to keep us occupied, plus the staff was very nice and laid back so when we broke out the Jenga and Connect Four sets, they didn't try and rush us out of there.

