83da7v9gQsWJegTW52qnuw
I came here as a part of a friend's birthday barhop last night and I have to say it met my low expectations.   The music was all the same (unce unce unce), the wait staff was dismissive, and the cocktails were terrible. All of our drinks were way too sweet - no mint leaves could be seen in my passion mojito... was it really even a mojito then? I didn't have any food, but my friends who did seemed satisfied with it despite it taking a while to come out. The lighting was virtually nonexistent, not even in the "setting the mood" good kind of way - we all had to break out our phone flashlights so we could be able to read the menus.  I would've given it only one star, but I decided it earned two because of the nice $5 arcade card check-in deal. Plus, we did get a nice view of post-baseball game fireworks show. Overall, though, I can't say I'll be very eager to return for anything except for the arcade games. It's just not my kind of place.

